43 SECTION 1.2.(a) G.S. 7B-201(a) reads as rewritten:
44 "(a) When the court obtains jurisdiction over a juvenile, jurisdiction shall continue until
45 terminated by order of the court or court, until the juvenile reaches the age of 18 years or is
46 otherwise emancipated, or upon the juvenile's death, whichever occurs first."
