1 (2) If the Division determines the conflict cannot be managed in the county that
2 receives the report, the Division shall appoint another county department that
3 shall assume management of the case. The county with the conflict of interest
4 bears the financial responsibility of the case unless otherwise agreed upon by
5 the counties involved in the conflict of interest.
6 (d) The county department of social services with the conflict of interest shall inform, in
7 writing, the parent, guardian, custodian, or caretaker of the conflict and the county that assumes
8 the management of the case. The written notice shall include the contact information for the
9 constituent concern line at the Division.
10 (e) If the county department of social services has a conflict of interest at the time of the
11 report or any time while managing the case and the county department of social services does not
12 refer the case to another county, a parent, guardian, custodian, caretaker, juvenile, or their
13 representative may seek to have the case transferred to another county by contacting the
14 constituent concern line at the Division, and the Division shall apply this section."
