31 SECTION 1.10.(a) G.S. 7B-101 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
32 "(14a) Legal counsel for the department. – An attorney representing the department
33 in proceedings under this Subchapter, regardless of whether the attorney is a
34 county attorney, department attorney, or contract attorney."
35 SECTION 1.10.(b) Article 6 of Subchapter I of Chapter 7B of the General Statutes
36 is amended by adding a new section to read:
37 "§ 7B-604. Legal counsel for department.
38 (a) The county department of social services shall be represented by legal counsel for the
39 department in proceedings governed by this Subchapter.
40 (b) Prior to representing the county department of social services in proceedings
41 governed by this Subchapter, legal counsel for the department shall complete a minimum of six
42 hours of training addressing State and federal child welfare law and procedures.
43 (c) The Division in consultation with (i) representatives of county directors and (ii) legal
44 counsel for the department who are department attorneys shall establish ongoing training and
45 practice standards that apply to legal counsel for the department."
