38 The clerk shall give notice of the hearing to the parties, the parties' attorneys, and the current
39 caretaker. The department of social services shall either provide to the clerk the name and address
40 of the juvenile's current caretaker for notice under this subsection or file written documentation
41 with the clerk that the juvenile's current caretaker was sent notice of hearing. The court shall
42 provide the current caretaker the opportunity to address the court, present evidence,
43 cross-examine witnesses, and be represented by an attorney at the caretaker's own expense.
44 Nothing in this subsection shall be construed to make the current caretaker a party to the
45 proceeding. The court may consider any evidence, including hearsay evidence as defined in
46 G.S. 8C-1, Rule 801, or testimony or evidence from any person that is not a party, that the court
47 finds to be relevant, reliable, and necessary to determine the needs of the juvenile. At the hearing
48 to review the change of placement, the court shall determine whether it is in the best interests of
49 the juvenile to be removed. This subsection shall not apply to cases when there are allegations of
50 abuse or neglect of the juvenile while under the care and supervision of the current caretaker.
