34 filing of a State N.C. Form D-400, or the equivalent.
35 (3c)(3d) "Family" means a unit consisting of a minor child or children and one or more
36 of their biological parents, adoptive parents, stepparents, or grandparents
37 living together. For purposes of the Work First Program, family also includes
38 a blood or half-blood relative or adoptive relative limited to brother, sister,
39 great-grandparent, great-great-grandparent, uncle, aunt, great-uncle,
40 great-aunt, great-great-uncle, great-great-aunt, nephew, niece, first cousin,
41 stepbrother, and stepsister.
42 (3d)(3e) "Federal TANF funds" means the Temporary Assistance for Needy Families
43 block grant funds provided for in Title IV-A of the Social Security Act.
44 (3f) Repealed by Session Laws 2009-489, s. 1, effective August 26, 2009.
45 (3e)(3g) "Fee-for-service program" means a payment model for the Medicaid program
46 operated by the Department of Health and Human Services pursuant to its
47 authority under Part 6 of Article 2 of Chapter 108A of the General Statutes in
48 which the Department pays enrolled providers for services provided to
49 Medicaid recipients rather than contracting for the coverage of services
50 through a capitated payment arrangement.
51
