33 PART IV. CRIMINAL HISTORY RECORD CHECK REQUIREMENT FOR
34 APPLICANTS OFFERED A POSITION FOR CITY AND COUNTY EMPLOYMENT
35 WORKING WITH CHILDREN
36 SECTION 4.1. G.S. 153A-94.2 reads as rewritten:
37 "§ 153A-94.2. Criminal history record checks of employees permitted.
38 (a) The board of commissioners may adopt or provide for rules and regulations or
39 ordinances concerning a requirement that any applicant for employment be subject to a criminal
40 history record check of State and National Repositories of Criminal Histories conducted by the
41 State Bureau of Investigation in accordance with G.S. 143B-1209.25 [G.S. 143B-1209.26].
42 G.S. 143B-1209.26. The local or regional public employer may consider the results of these
43 criminal history record checks in its hiring decisions.
44 (b) Notwithstanding the provisions of subsection (a) of this section, if the position being
45 filled requires an applicant for employment to work with children in any capacity, the board of
46 commissioners shall require the applicant, if offered the position, be subject to a criminal history
47 record check conducted by the State Bureau of Investigation in accordance with
48 G.S. 143B-1209.26. The local or regional public employer must extend a conditional offer of the
49 position pending the results of a criminal history record check required by this section."
50 SECTION 4.2. G.S. 160A-164.2 reads as rewritten:
51 "§ 160A-164.2. Criminal history record check of employees permitted.
House Bill 612-Fifth Edition Page 31

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (a) The council may adopt or provide for rules and regulations or ordinances concerning
2 a requirement that any applicant for employment be subject to a criminal history record check of
3 State and National Repositories of Criminal Histories conducted by the State Bureau of
4 Investigation in accordance with G.S. 143B-1209.25 [G.S. 143B-1209.26]. G.S. 143B-1209.26.
5 The city may consider the results of these criminal history record checks in its hiring decisions.
6 (b) Notwithstanding the provisions of subsection (a) of this section, if the position being
7 filled requires an applicant for employment to work with children in any capacity, the council
8 shall require the applicant, if offered the position, be subject to a criminal history record check
9 conducted by the State Bureau of Investigation in accordance with G.S. 143B-1209.26. The city
10 must extend a conditional offer of the position pending the results of a criminal history record
11 check required by this section."
12 SECTION 4.3. Sections 4.1 and 4.2 of this act would become effective October 1,
13 2025, and would apply to offers of employment on or after that date.
